    <!-- Page Title, Problem Description, and Symptoms -->
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-xl-6 text-center mx-auto">
        <!-- Title in one line -->
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold mb-4" style="line-height: 1.2; color: #260d5e;">
          How to Handle a Heatstroke in an Emergency
        </h1>
        <!-- Brief problem description -->
        <p class="lead text-muted">
          Heatstroke is a severe condition caused by prolonged exposure to high temperatures.
          Immediate cooling measures are essential to prevent serious complications.
        </p>
        <!-- Short symptoms section in red -->
        <p class="fs-5" style="color: red;">
          <strong>Symptoms:</strong> Extremely high body temperature, hot dry skin, confusion, and rapid heartbeat.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Main Content: Do's and What Not To Do -->
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <!-- Left Column: Guidelines -->
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3">Immediate Steps (Do's):</h3>
        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Move to a Cooler Area:</strong> Immediately take the person to a shaded or air-conditioned place.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cool the Body:</strong> Remove excess clothing and apply cool, damp cloths to the skin.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Hydrate:</strong> Encourage small sips of cool water if the person is conscious.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Fan the Person:</strong> Use a fan or any available means to help lower their body temperature.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Call Emergency Services:</strong> Dial your local emergency number immediately.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Do not use ice or extremely cold water directly on the skin.</li>
          <li>Avoid sudden temperature changes that could shock the body.</li>
          <li>Do not delay calling for professional help.</li>
          <li>Do not force fluids if the person is too disoriented.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted mt-3">
          <em>Note:</em> This guide is for emergency use only and does not replace professional medical treatment.
        </p>
      </div>
      
